    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-01T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-01T13:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00 Revolutions/106: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MWJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-01T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 1, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. The three communist leaders <persName corresp="#p_MA1">Marti</persName>,
                        <persName>Luna</persName> and <persName>Zapata</persName> after condemnation
                    by court martial were publicly executed this morning in the cemetery in
                    Salvador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McCafferty</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
